Subject: [liste-egc] EDBT Summer School 2013 Call for Participation



CALL FOR PARTICIPATION
Data all around:  Big, Linked, Open, ...
EDBT Summer School 2013
Aussois, France 1- 6th September 2013
http://edbt-school-2013.imag.fr/
Contact: edbt.school.2013@imag.fr
APPLICATION DEADLINE: 15th April, 2013

* * * * * * * * Fellowships available ! Apply now !! * * * * * * * * * * *

The EDBT Summer School brings together leading researchers recognized as leading experts in their fields and provides participants the opportunity to gain deeper insight into current research trends in the database area.

In 2013, the school focus will be data all around: big, linked open, ... The scientific topics will cover large-scale data storage and processing in the areas of social networks and open data. The school will be organized as a combination of lectures, hands-on tutorials and a series of talks.

Granted students will present posters and for the first time, students can express their creativity by participating in a research challenge. The school will cover the following topics:
-	Polyglot Persistence
-	Managing Big Data
-	Social Networks
-	Social Networks Analytics
More information on these topics is available at
http://edbt-school-2013.imag.fr/

SPEAKERS

- Michel Adiba, Professor Emeritus, University Joseph Fourier
- Franois Bancilhon, CEO, Data Publica
- Francesco Bonchi, Senior Research Scientist, Yahoo! Research Barcelona
- Djoerd Hiemstra, Professor at University of Twente
- Laks V.S. Lakshmanan, Professor at University of British Columbia
- Genoveva Vargas-Solar, Full time researcher CNRS, LIG-LAFMIA Labs
- Roberto Zicari, Prof. at University of Frankfurt


PARTICIPATION

The target audience of the school is advanced graduate and PhD students, post-doctoral researchers, and may include few academic and industrial researchers, and developers. The school will be open to about 100 qualified, motivated and pre-selected candidates.

Participants will be selected according to the order of registration, the quality of the submitted request and the institution of provenance to ensure a balanced group of people. PhD students will have to send a copy of their student card at registration time.

Interested students must apply by providing a rsum and a one-page description of their research and motivation at:

https://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=edbtschool2013

The school fee is 600 Euro. The fee includes all courses, hand-out material, coffee/tea breaks, social events and accommodation. The EDBT Association will provide a limited number of grants covering school fee only or school fee and accommodation. Those interested on school fellowships must give arguments in their motivation letter.

Bursaries will be awarded based upon the background and the scientific performance of the applicants. The economic development level of applicant institutions will also be considered.

IMPORTANT DATES
-	Deadline for application: 15th April, 2013
-	Notification of acceptance for participation and grants: 15th May, 2013
-	Deadline for registration: 30th June, 2013
-	13th EDBT Summer School: 1st- 6th September, 2013



